## Notes

The YouTube upload guide requires OAuth 2.0 authorization for uploads, and the thumbnail endpoint is a separate API call after the main upload returns a `videoId`. [2][3] Render supports Docker-based web services, so this file fits the Docker deployment path you already have. [1]

For your quiz format, this version should work well for mobile-first vertical content because it uses 1080x1920 output, short timed clips, and a simple custom thumbnail structure that follows YouTube’s guidance to keep thumbnails readable and visually distinct. [4][3]

